# üìÑ Modern Industrial Resume Guide (2026 Edition)

> **How to translate shop-floor "know-how" into a recruiter-ready resume.**

## üéØ The Formula for Success
In today's industrial market, listing "Repaired machines" is no longer enough. You must show the **impact** of your tacit knowledge and your ability to work with new tech.

### Use the "Action + Context = Impact" Bullet Point:
- **Weak:** "Used Digital Twins for maintenance."
- **Strong:** "Leveraged **Digital Twin simulations** to troubleshoot pump failures 24 hours faster than manual methods, reducing downtime by 15%."

---

## üõ†Ô∏è Key Skills to Include in 2026
Don't just list "Hard Worker." Group your skills into these modern categories:

| Category | Skills to List |
| :--- | :--- |
| **Advanced Tech** | Digital Twins, PLC Programming, Predictive Maintenance (PdM), Robotics Oversight |
| **AI & Data** | Human-in-the-Loop (HITL), Agentic AI Workflows, IoT Sensor Monitoring |
| **Traditional Mastery** | Tacit Knowledge Transfer, Blueprints/Schematics, Specialized Tool Calibration |
| **Operations** | Lean Six Sigma, OSHA Safety Leadership, Changeover Optimization |

---

## üìù Example Summary for Candidates
> "Result-driven **Maintenance Lead** with 10+ years of experience bridging traditional mechanical expertise with **Agentic AI** diagnostics. Proven track record of capturing **Tacit Knowledge** from veteran teams to reduce onboarding time by 20%. Expert in using **Digital Twins** to simulate and prevent costly equipment failures."

---

## ‚úÖ Final Checklist Before You Apply
- [ ] **PDF Format:** Always save as a PDF to keep your formatting perfect.
- [ ] **Quantify:** Did you save money? Did you save time? Use numbers ($ and %).
- [ ] **GitHub Link:** Include the link to this repository so they can see your interest in industry trends!

